flowchart TB
    N1["1. Technical objective: Rust client SDK for building tools and services that talk to Neo N4 APIs."]
    N2["2. Determinism: same configuration and user intent produce the same request or package"]
    N3["3. Input constraints: developer app | gateway endpoint | wallet/config"]
    N4["4. Transition rule: requests, configs, packages, or reports advance through checked stages"]
    N5["5. Verifiable output: typed client result | transaction request | query response"]
    N6["6. Minimal trust: trust validation and signing policy, not unchecked user input"]
    N7["7. Layer separation: interface, encoding, network submission, and diagnostics are separated"]
    N8["8. Observable evidence: command, config digest, network, output artifacts, and diagnostics"]
    N1 --> N2
    N1 --> N3
    N1 --> N4
    N1 --> N5
    N1 --> N6
    N1 --> N7
    N1 --> N8
    N2 -. constrains .-> N4
    N4 -. produces .-> N5
    N5 -. consumed by .-> N6
